      "rdfs:comment": [
        "NOTE: Categories are not content until they are written down.",
        "EXAMPLE: The literary work 'The Adventures of Huckleberry Finn' by Mark Twain, independent of any particular edition.",
        "DEFINITION: Information available in some medium.",
        "NOTE: This class includes both abstract content and its expression, but it must have at least one expression in order to be content. For example, the idea a writer has for a book is not content until it is expressed in some form, but a single content object may have multiple expressions - e.g., the particular print and audio editions."
      ],
      "rdfs:isDefinedBy": {
